---
## Content

The src folder is found in the Project view and contains all codes (application code and android unit test script) and resource files for the following subdirectories: 

*	AndroidTest is a directory for Instrumentation unit test that can run on an Android device or emulator. These 
  test have access to Instrumentation information such as context of the app testing. 
* Test is a unit tests that run locally on the Java Virtual Machine. These test can be used to minimize
  execution time when the tests have no Android framework dependencies or when you duplicate the Android framework dependencies. Unit test should be under the src/test/java
*Main contains the source files involving:
		*Java folder contains all the java codes
		* res contains drawables and layouts


---
## Practice

What is AndroidTest?
???

* Used for Instrumentation unit test. 
* Contains source files
* run locally on the Java Virtual Machine

